Ethel May Halls https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethel_May_Halls 0 Ethyl May Halls (born November 20, 1882 in California - died September 16, 1967 in Hollywood, California) was an American film and theatre actress for nearly 70 years. After being a Florodora girl she worked for Biograph Studios for several years in films with among others Mary Pickford and Rudolph Valentino. She appeared in many bit parts in Hollywood right up until the 1940s.
